
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hipercdecode` baraye decode kardane payam-haye encode shode ba format hiperc estefade mishavad.  In dastoor bishtar dar barname-haye radioee ke az protocol-haye khas estefade mikonand karbord darad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-i <file>`  --> 📥 Gereftane dade az yek file be jaye voroodi standart.
    🔹 `-o <file>`  --> 📤 Neveshtane natije decode shode dar yek file be jaye khorooji standart.
    🔹 `-v`        --> 📢 Namayeshe etela'ate bishtar dar morede decode shodan.
    🔹 `-h`        --> ℹ️ Namayeshe rahnama va komak.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hipercdecode < input.hiperc

    🔹 Decode kardane dade az `input.hiperc` va chap kardane natije dar terminal.

    $ hipercdecode -i input.hiperc -o output.txt

    🔹 Decode kardane dade az `input.hiperc` va zakhire kardane natije dar `output.txt`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hipercdecode -v < sample.hiperc

    🔹 Decode kardane dade az `sample.hiperc` va namayeshe etela'ate bishtar dar morede process decode dar terminal.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hipercdecode` command is used to decode messages encoded in the HiPerC format. This command is often used in radio applications that use specific protocols.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-i <file>`  --> 📥 Take input data from a file instead of standard input.
    🔹 `-o <file>`  --> 📤 Write the decoded output to a file instead of standard output.
    🔹 `-v`        --> 📢 Display verbose information about the decoding process.
    🔹 `-h`        --> ℹ️ Display help and usage information.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hipercdecode < input.hiperc

    🔹 Decode data from `input.hiperc` and print the result to the terminal.

    $ hipercdecode -i input.hiperc -o output.txt

    🔹 Decode data from `input.hiperc` and save the result to `output.txt`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hipercdecode -v < sample.hiperc

    🔹 Decode data from `sample.hiperc` and display verbose information about the decoding process in the terminal.
